80":"1280","abt 1300":"about 1300","London, Lond., Eng.":"London, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hend","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["1  English: (i) nickname from Middle English  <i>hende</i> (Old English  <i>gehænd</i>) ‘courtly, courteous, refined’. (ii) relationship name, perhaps occasionally a variant of   Henn   (a pet form of Henry) with an excrescent  <i>-d</i>. Compare the pet form  <i>Hendekin</i> (  see  Henkin  ) and the patronymic surname   Henderson   for  <i>Henryson</i>.","2  English: variant of   End   with a prosthetic  <i>H-</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Henkin","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Doron, Hyman.","English (Middlesex): from the Middle English personal name <i>Henekin</i>, <i>Hendekin</i>, a pet form of   Henry  . Compare   Hankin   1 and   Henn  .","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): metronymic from the female personal name <i>Khenke</i> (a pet form of Yiddish <i>Khane</i>, from Hebrew <i>Ḥanna</i>; see   Hanna   6) + the Slavic possessive suffix <i>-in</i>."]},{"name":"End","meanings":["English: topographic name from Middle English <i>(atten) ende</i>, denoting someone who lived at the end of a village or other settlement."]},{"name":"Henderson","meanings":["English and Scottish: usually from Middle English and Older Scots <i>Hener(i)son</i> ‘Henry's son’, occasionally from Middle English <i>Hendeson</i> ‘son of <i>Hen</i>’, a pet form of   Henry  , both with an intrusive <i>-d-</i>. Compare   Hendrie  . In Scotland <i>Henderson</i> was sometimes substituted for   McKendrick  ."]},{"name":"Henn","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Helmut, Otto, Siegfried, Ulrike, Aloysius, Bernhard, Heinz, Hermann, Herta, Jurgen, Kurt, Manfred.","English: from the personal name <i>Henn</i>, which, like <i>Hann</i>, was a pet form of <i>Henry</i>. Compare   Henkin  .","English: nickname from Middle English <i>hen(ne)</i> ‘hen’ (Old English <i>henn</i>, related to <i>hana</i> ‘cock’), for someone thought to resemble a hen in some way, or perhaps from Middle English <i>hen</i> ‘poor man, rascal’."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. John Hend was born about 1280. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with John Hend."},"et":{"abt 1280–":"umbes 1280–Surnud","1278–Male":"1278–Surnud","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","1302–Female":"1302–Surnud","1280–Female":"1280–Surnud","abt 1302":"umbes 1302","1302":"1302","1300":"1300","1278":"1278","abt 1280":"umbes 1280","1280":"1280","abt 1300":"umbes 1300","London, Lond., Eng.":"London, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"abt 1280–":"noin 1280–Kuollut","1278–Male":"1278–Kuollut","1300–Male":"1300–Kuollut","1302–Female":"1302–Kuollut","1280–Female":"1280–Kuollut","abt 1302":"noin 1302","1302":"1302","1300":"1300","1278":"1278","abt 1280":"noin 1280","1280":"1280","abt 1300":"noin 1300","London, Lond., Eng.":"London, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"abt 1280–":"environ 1280–Décédée","1278–Male":"1278–Décédé","1300–Male":"1300–Décédé","1302–Female":"1302–Décédée","1280–Female":"1280–Décédée","abt 1302":"environ 1302","1302":"1302","1300":"1300","1278":"1278","abt 1280":"environ 1280","1280":"1280","abt 1300":"environ 1300","London, Lond., Eng.":"Londres, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs. John Hend est née environ 1280. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils et 1 fille avec John Hend."},"de":{"abt 1280–":"um 1280–Verstorben","1278–Male":"1278–Verstorben","1300–Male":"1300–Verstorben","1302–Female":"1302–Verstorben","1280–Female":"1280–Verstorben","abt 1302":"um 1302","1302":"1302","1300":"1300","1278":"1278","abt 1280":"um 1280","1280":"1280","abt 1300":"um 1300","London, Lond., Eng.":"London, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Mrs. John Hend wurde um 1280 geboren. Sie hatte mit John Hend mindestens 1 Sohn u